  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Scholarship for Zaman Tare research support year one and two</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">CAFOD has obtained funding from the European Union for the implementation of a program promoting tolerance, known as &#x2018;ZAMAN TARE&#x2019;. This programme aims to strengthen multiculturalism and religious tolerance in Niger, through various initiatives. One such initiative is to: Support Master&apos;s students to conduct research on cultural and religious pluralism in Niger. 
As part of this project, CAFOD is pleased to announce the availability of 30 research support grants for the 2018/2019 and 2019/2020 academic year. These scholarships are intended for master&apos;s students and aim to contribute to the understanding of the factors that allow religious tolerance and multiculturalism as well as those that hinder them with a view to developing policies that can strengthen multiculturalism and tolerance in Niger.</narrative>
  </description>
